The paper deals with the problem of computing upward drawings of trees, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The concept of pathwidth is also mentioned, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.TH) and optimization (cs.SI). However, since the focus of the paper is on the geometric aspect of the problem, we believe that cs.CG and cs.DS are the most likely categories.
